      "lesson title": "When AI Meets Heavy Machinery",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson introduces learners to the growing use of artificial intelligence in heavy agricultural and industrial machinery, including tractors, drilling systems, and autonomous equipment. We will explore how AI is being used to automate and assist with tasks that were traditionally carried out by human operators, and why this shift brings both exciting opportunities and serious risks. You will gain a clear understanding of the types of hazards that can arise when AI systems interact with large, powerful machines in unpredictable environments. The lesson is designed for beginners, so no prior technical knowledge is required, just a willingness to think carefully about safety in an increasingly automated world. By the end, you will be better equipped to recognise the risks associated with AI-assisted machinery and understand why proper oversight, training, and regulation are so important.",
